Package edu.umn.nlpie.mtap.processing

Class DocumentProcessor

java.lang.Object
edu.umn.nlpie.mtap.processing.ProcessorBase
edu.umn.nlpie.mtap.processing.EventProcessor
edu.umn.nlpie.mtap.processing.DocumentProcessor
Direct Known Subclasses:
HelloWorldExample, WordOccurrencesExampleProcessor
public abstract class DocumentProcessor
extends EventProcessor
Abstract base class for a processor of Document objects.

Example: 

     @Processor('example-processor')
     public class ExampleProcessor extends DocumentProcessor {
       @Override
       protected void process(Document document, JsonObject params, JsonObject.Builder result) {
         // do processing on document
       }
     }

The no-argument default constructor is required for instantiation via reflection. At runtime, the process(Document, JsonObject, JsonObjectBuilder) method may be called simultaneously from multiple threads, so the implementing class is responsible for ensuring thread-safety.
